./turing <input file>
 - set turing machine coded in <input file> running on empty tape
 - input file must be a compiled file
./turing -c <input file> <output file>
 - compile a turing machine, .tmsrc file
 - output file should have the extension .tm
./turing -i <input file>

Flags:
 -h, --help: display help screen
 -c <input file> <output file>: compile turing machine
 -d <input file> <output file>: decompile turing machine
 -i <input file>: run in interactive mode
 -m <nsteps>: stop after a maximum of <nsteps> steps
 -t <string>: set tape to <string> as initial configuration

Interactive mode:
 -n: next
 -n <number>: next <number> configurations
 -u <state name>: all configurations until in state <state name>
 -s: in combination with any other flag: skip all except last
